product: Cheez-It, Baked Snack Cheese Crackers, White Cheddar, Family Size, 21 Oz
author: 69Pace,
comment: Cheeze-It is our favorite brand for cheese crackers. The authentic cheese flavor keeps us coming back to it. The White Cheddar flavor has the right combination of white cheddar cheese flavor, crunchiness and salt. Although it does leave a slight cheese residue on your fingers, it not as much as other fake cheese snacks would leave and stain your fingers. The 45-pouch box is great for families to have handy to provide snacks for lunches, work or on-the-go. Each pouch has a generous number of crackers which was enough to curve my appetite when eaten as a snack and a perfect side for a lunch. The white cheddar flavor is indulging. Although each pouch helps with portion control, it is so easy to eat another pouch! In addition to being the perfect size snack, it can also be used in recipes. My wife used two pouches, crumbled the crackers and sprinkled it over her homemade mac-and-cheese prior to baking it. It was delicious! I highly recommend these and are much healthier because they are baked and made with 100% real cheese. [This review was collected as part of a promotion.]

product: Nabisco Sweet Treats Cookie Variety Pack OREO, OREO Golden & CHIPS AHOY!, 30 Snack Packs
author: Reneeg,
comment: First time ordering this variety pack and I loved the different flavors. I never had golden oreos before and they are really good. The portions are nice and I like that I can stick them in my bag for when I am on the go. I love Oreo cookies but the problem is......If I buy a regular pack of Oreo cookie, I might eat half the pack at once. The box contains 30 packs of Oreo (10 chocolate, 10 vanilla, and 10 Oreo cookies). These comes with individual packages and each package contains 2 cookies. I love these because I can bring 1 pack to work so I can control how much I eat. Good snack for the day.

product: Nabisco Sweet Treats Cookie Variety Pack OREO, OREO Golden & CHIPS AHOY!, 30 Snack Packs
author: Reneeg,
comment: First time ordering this variety pack and I loved the different flavors. I never had golden oreos before and they are really good. The portions are nice and I like that I can stick them in my bag for when I am on the go. I love Oreo cookies but the problem is......If I buy a regular pack of Oreo cookie, I might eat half the pack at once. The box contains 30 packs of Oreo (10 chocolate, 10 vanilla, and 10 Oreo cookies). These comes with individual packages and each package contains 2 cookies. I love these because I can bring 1 pack to work so I can control how much I eat. Good snack for the day.

One very large box with plenty of craft/butcher paper as protection (which we will use as Thanksgiving table 'cloth' or Christmas gift wrap). No complaints!

product: Utz Halloween Mini Cheddar Cheese Ball Barrel, 60 Ct (0.25 Oz, Bags)

author: cs,
comment: I bought these last year and loved them so bought more this year. The price is great, the tiny cheese balls are delicious and perfect for giving out. I bought a container for the office and everyone loves them. Will also be giving them out along with candy on Halloween to the kids. I even use the purple containers at Halloween by putting a little fake candle in them and setting them on the porch. Instant decorations!!

product: Utz Halloween Mini Cheddar Cheese Ball Barrel, 60 Ct (0.25 Oz, Bags)
author: Scott P,
comment: Quick delivery and great price

product: Utz Halloween Mini Cheddar Cheese Ball Barrel, 60 Ct (0.25 Oz, Bags)
author: Crys,
comment: Price for amount is not the best deal but when I get little trick or treaters who can't have (or don't want candy) choose these and then go running to their dad in the street joyfully saying "DAD! I got cheese balls!!!"

product: Utz Halloween Mini Cheddar Cheese Ball Barrel, 60 Ct (0.25 Oz, Bags)
author: KImmi,
comment: I bought these for our work desk trick or treating festivities. My coworkers liked them and especially that it was something different from all of the chocolate in the office. Only 4 stars cuz the individual bags were a little smaller then what I was expecting but there were a lot in the container so I gave 2 bags to everyone.

product: Utz Halloween Mini Cheddar Cheese Ball Barrel, 60 Ct (0.25 Oz, Bags)
author: Tracy,
comment: Purchased these for a company party. The kids were saying they didn't taste good so I looked at expiration date and they expire Nov 2016. I tried them myself and they were stale and chewy. Not fresh at all. Not sure if these were left from last years inventory. I will be returning the other 2 buckets I planned on passing out on Halloween. Very disappointing.

product: Utz Halloween Mini Cheddar Cheese Ball Barrel, 60 Ct (0.25 Oz, Bags)
author: Loosie,
comment: This container of Cheetos minis is the right size of cheese balls for my toddler grandchildren as well as for the other members of my family. Fresh and crispy. Yummy

product: Utz Halloween Mini Cheddar Cheese Ball Barrel, 60 Ct (0.25 Oz, Bags)

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz
author: Cocochugs,
comment: These are the best cashews ever! I purchase other "name brand" nuts and they were tiny and all broken up. Some of their reviews even said they had bugs in them. They were also heavily salted. These are nice large nuts, very, very few broken and they are lightly salted, which I like. These are also a great price. I highly recommend these.

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz
author: Courtney,
comment: I love these cashews! I don't like too much salt, and these aren't as salty as some other brands, I've tried. Plus, the cashews are actually softer, too.

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz
author: GrammyC,
comment: My husband loves these cashews so I order them frequently to be shipped to our home. He says they are as good as the name brand cashews but much cheaper.

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz
author: BARBARA,
comment: The cashews are very good, but the container is heavy and should not have been in the same carton as my 2 boxes of cereal and 1 pkg of cookies. They were crushed!

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz
author: DarkInNY,
comment: These were some of the best cashews I have ever had. I was shocked at how fresh and good. Better than some I pay more than double the price for. Will definitely buy again.

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz
author: outsidethelines,
comment: YUM! What can I say? What could possible be even remotely bad about 30 oz of cashews! I separated them into snack bags so I wouldn't over indulge, but they are not even considered a guilty pleasure. They are downright good for your health. I'm really happy I purchased these. I figure I saved at least $20 by purchasing them in such a large quantity.

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz
author: taylormade66,
comment: Got these as a birthday gift for myself ! They were fresh. The cashews were 99% whole, until I got to the bottom of the container. Then there were some broken salty pieces. Would buy again.

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz
author: LoveTheGreatValues,
comment: Good value, and the cashews are whole and have a good flavor. So nice to get them delivered and in a protective, reusable container, too.

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz

comment: These cashew nuts were very good. But it was a nuisance each time to have to wash off all the excess salt. I have stopped buying these and am now buying unsalted nuts from Target.

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz
author: GINGERRED,
comment: This item came in a strange packaging. The container was not sealed. I returned to the store. I like the nuts themselves, just that I believe that it was known the seal was non existant as they put the jar in a plastic bag then into a cardboard box to ship.

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz
author: Haleemah,
comment: It tastes like cashew haha. It came with very few broken pieces and that's amazing. It's a good deal at the price.

product: Great Value Deluxe Cashews, 30 oz
author: Savingscatcher,

comment: Was skeptical while ordering as from past experience many a time got rotten or very bad tasting cashews mostly from sealed cans and packets. But this one was excellent. The right roast,just light salt and good quality goes anywhere.

author: happyintexas,
comment: So I bought these for our Uncle Sonny who is in a Secaucus, NJ Nursing Home. He loves to give people things and I try to send him something fun to give out for Halloween to both the residents and the staff. They are all wonderful! Since I am in Texas, his wonderful Social Coordinator on staff offered to go pick them up at the Secaucus, NJ Sams for me and deliver them to Uncle Sonny's room. I called him thinking he would hold onto them until....you guessed it....Halloween. He called and was so excited because everyone he gave one to LOVED THEM and according to him WAS A BIG HIT! So, if you will let the Manager know at the Secuccus, NJ SAMS that Anthony Rossi in Room 231P is in need of more goodies including these wonderful "Big Hit" Halloween Pretzels to pass out to all residents and his wonderful staff again on Halloween Eve! Thanks, Kathy Rossi

product: Pringles, Potato Crisps Chips, Original, 5.2 Oz
author: ThePhlegmAndMucusMaster,
comment: I believe this item cost $1.44. A Great Value (Wal-Mart brand) 12oz. can of tuna fish is like $1.58, almost the same price as the can of Pringles, but you can't ever get the much more healthier option (the tuna fish), delivered, over the can of potato chips, online, and the one you can store for long periods of time. During hostile, dangerous, combative, sketchy, scary times, like COVID-19/coronavirus outbreaks, Wal-Mart needs to make essential food staples, on the ready, for their local population via their online source, w/much higher limits, like '10', instead of only one, or often times 'none' ('sold out'). Canned tuna, canned salmon, Great Value dry roasted, and honey roasted, peanuts, all of which either have ONE ITEM LIMITS, or are consistently SOLD OUT. Another type of health food I like a lot (*sarcasm alert*) are the Great Value version of 'Pop-Tarts', which are much better and cheaper than the Kellogg's name brand, and yes, often sold out too.

product: Pringles, Potato Crisps Chips, Original, 5.2 Oz
author: NunyaBis,
comment: I gave this 1-star rating, ---- really a 0 star, BUT i see you automatically force 2 stars on a person when they only select a 1-star rating on your products. And about these chips: all of the Pringles were broken into crumbs in each canister, except 8 of them --- a person would have to use a SPOON to eat these!!!! And why does the back "Nutrition Facts" Label, look so yellow-dingy, as if it was sitting in someone's garage for 60 years? And i know the products that i shop for (it's content and packaging), and the clear plastic 'lid' on these Pringles cans seems to be a different kind of [hard] plastic, as opposed to softer, bendable, plastic lid,.... it seems counterfeit! --- Oh wait! what do i see here?! some type of Chinese, or Thailand print on the back of the can, why is that, Walmart?! Are there any regulations, and Quality-Control pertaining to these products. Where's the integrity, honesty, ?! .....In year 2017, things seemed to be different, in a Negative way, in America regarding integrity, and doing the right things towards Citizens and Consumers who, both: are tax-payers; and who PAY FOR THEIR STORE ITEMS, INCLUDING LOCAL TAXES ON EACH ITEM; and INCLUDING SHIPPING/DELIVERY!!!! product: RITZ Fresh Stacks Original Crackers, Family Size, 17.8 oz
author: john,
comment: There's nothing I didn't like about these crackers...they're RITZ so they have to be good. Great with soups or great all by themselves. Might try putting peanut butter and jelly on them for a walk back to a time when you were a kid and your mom put half-a-dozen of them together in your lunch box. Cheese goes good with them, too. My niece likes dipping them in Ranch Dressing. You get the idea.

product: RITZ Fresh Stacks Original Crackers, Family Size, 17.8 oz
author: Deen,
comment: The light buttery crispness of a Ritz in convenient stay-fresh packs that are about half the size of regular packs. Great for individual servings. Some things can't be substituted and I think these crackers fit in that category. Eat them as a snack, in soup, in a casserole or try other uses like a chocolate-peanut butter-banana Ritz.

product: RITZ Fresh Stacks Original Crackers, Family Size, 17.8 oz
author: Ivanya,
comment: All the goodness of Ritz crackers in a smaller size package is the only thing I have to say. These half packs are the perfect size as a snack by themselves or as a single serving side with a sandwich. Good for 2 as a movie night snacker with cheese or other combo too. It keeps the crackers fresh all the time. I'm a big fan of these fresh stacks.

product: RITZ Fresh Stacks Original Crackers, Family Size, 17.8 oz
comment: Great for snacking. The individually packaged little "sleeves" of crackers are good to have, so that you can keep the others in the box fresh, while enjoying eating some....

The only thing that I would change is the individual cracker size. When I first started eating them all those years ago, they were much bigger. Now I can get a whole one into my mouth (when no-one is looking).

product: Cheez-It, Cheesy Baked Snacks, Double Cheese, 7.5 Oz
author: CruxisRex,
comment: we tried to Flavors. Double cheese, and sour cream. Both were a disappointment. Starting with the good, of which there is only one point, we really enjoyed the light crispy texture of these. Now for the not so good. Neither of these flavors, and this is NOT an exaggeration, had even the faintest hint of cheese flavor. Literally none. Even the most bland store brand cheesy snacks put these to shame. these may be the least cheesiest cheesy snack I've ever had. after eating a few, I was getting a familiar flavor. Pringles. They taste a lot like Pringles. They have that artificial potato sludge flavor. A look at the ingredients confirms it. There is potato in these. perhaps it's to get that crispy texture, or perhaps it's just too cut the mix with cheap low-quality ingredients, but it's not pleasant. the sour cream ones were slightly better because of the seasoning, but the double cheese ones tasted like unseasoned Pringles. If you're looking for a Cheesy snack, this isn't it. If that's what you want, you're better off with normal Cheez-Its, or what I prefer, Planters cheez balls.

product: Cheez-It, Cheesy Baked Snacks, Double Cheese, 7.5 Oz
author: LoriA,
comment: At first bite these were not at all what I expected. I even looked at the label-twice-to be sure I had bought the Double Cheese flavor that I wanted! What I got instead was a very thin and crispy little cracker that tasted overwhelmingly like garlic, sour cream, and onion. That's why I checked the label twice, and why I came back here to read the description. This chip tasted nothing at all like a Cheez-it! Why would I buy a chip with the Cheez-it name if it doesn't taste like that product? Nowhere does it state that it will taste like sour cream and onion chips. I expect garlic as a basic seasoning, but not as strong as this had. After searching through the ingredients list I did find those flavors, stating it contained less than 2%. It sure tasted like more to me. What my 2¡Ù opinions came down to was that I liked the crispy texture and bite of these chips. But I'll be giving them to a friend because I wanted cheese-flavored Cheez-it taste. Not sour cream, onion, and garlic chips. I didn't get what the label claimed was inside the bag.

author: Krista,

No wonder they don't carry other trail mix; then no one would buy this (the Walmart brand). I'm getting trail mix elsewhere.

author: donna,

Some bags have raisins that are salted. I do not like salted raisins. If I wanted a salted snack, I would eat chips. Also, in some bags the raisins are tiny, too dried, and have a bitter taste. I usually pick these out.

product: Great Value Mountain Trail Mix, 26 Oz.

I just finished the bag that I bought from there so I will go back to Walmart and get some more they are awesome they are also low in calories..
